sentences: Mark Pritchard (born 1971) is an English electronic musician, currently signed to Warp.
Mark Pritchard was born in Yeovil in Somerset, England in 1971.
Pritchard and Middleton formed a record label, Evolution (named after one of Carl Craig's tracks), in 1991.

In June 2013, it was announced that he would be retiring his various aliases and using solely his birth name for future releases, with which, Pritchard released a trio of EPs on Warp, all a medley of footwork, jungle and bass-heavy dance-floor orientated electronics.

A full-length LP, Under the Sun was released in 2016, and its companion album The Four Worlds in 2018, both on Warp; deeply atmospheric and richly impressionistic, hearkening back to Pritchard's work as Global Communication, with key vocal features from Thom Yorke, Linda Perhacs, Bibio, and Beans.

A full-length LP, Under the Sun was released in 2016, and its companion album The Four Worlds in 2018, both on Warp; deeply atmospheric and richly impressionistic, hearkening back to Pritchard's work as Global Communication, with key vocal features from Thom Yorke, Linda Perhacs, Bibio, and Beans.
The Link material goes back to 1992's The First Link EP, and is predominantly techno, often using drum breaks in favour of classic 808 and 909 drum sounds.
The Link alias also spawned Link & E621, which referred to Pritchard and Tom Middleton and was used for the 1995 release Antacid.
The Reload alias was born in 1991 and was responsible for some of Pritchard's more industrial output.
Under this alias, several EPs and remixes were produced, and the 1993 album A Collection of Short Stories.
Pritchard has released under this alias through Warp since 2008.
Pritchard first released solo material under his birth name with 2009's ? /

Following releases on Hyperdub and Deep Medi Musik, he is currently signed to Warp, through which he released a trilogy of EP's exploring styles such as footwork and jungle in 2013, followed by two ambient companion albums Under The Sun in 2016 and The Four Worlds in 2018.

Perhaps their most well known release was 1996's The Way / The Deep EP, considered by some to be a house classic.
A project with Tom Middleton, Jedi Knights first appeared remixing the Link & E621 track Antacid in 1995.
The pair released three singles under this alais from 1998 to 2001.
This one-off collaboration resulted in the 2000 single The Drained / Migraine.
They released three singles between 1993 and 1997.
This was a predominantly ambient project with Opus III vocalist Kirsty Hawkshaw, and resulted in the 1997 release Isolation.
Pricthard went on to produce Hawkshaw's debut album with Dave Brinkworth, and in 2004, Pritchard contributed to Hawkshaw's Ambient Vocals.
A UK #61 chart hit followed in 'Monkey' in 1992.
This was a collaborative project with Dave Brinkworth that started in 1998.
Pritchard and grime MC Trim teamed up for the Planet Mu single Stereotype in 2011.
Pritchard collaborated with Wiley on the 2012 single "Scar/Moneyman," released by Ninja Tune.

In the late '90s, he started collaborating with Dave Brinkworth spawning the projects Use of Weapons and Harmonic 33.
This NYC house project was inspired by Strictly Rhythm's early 1990s releases, particularly those of DJ Pierre.
Mark Pritchard (born 1971) is an English electronic musician, currently signed to Warp.
From an early age he listened to a wide range of musical styles, and says when he was 5 his mother would buy him a new 7" record every week.
After spending his school years listening to ska, 2-tone, indie and rock, he eventually became involved in club music, specifically Detroit techno and Chicago house.

A full-length LP, Under the Sun was released in 2016, and its companion album The Four Worlds in 2018, both on Warp; deeply atmospheric and richly impressionistic, hearkening back to Pritchard's work as Global Communication, with key vocal features from Thom Yorke, Linda Perhacs, Bibio, and Beans.
The Troubleman material was released through Far Out Recordings from 2001-2005.

Following releases on Hyperdub and Deep Medi Musik, he is currently signed to Warp, through which he released a trilogy of EP's exploring styles such as footwork and jungle in 2013, followed by two ambient companion albums Under The Sun in 2016 and The Four Worlds in 2018.
Stylistically, the releases explored "...exotica, '60s/'70s library music, sci-fi, ...hip-hop".
